<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: A Tunare Shaman</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-06 17:32:37</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I got mine for 60pp a few days ago. Quite a sweetheart deal, I think.  I wanted to say that I think debuffs that slow a mob's attack speed, like Walking Sleep, are underestimated.  Intuitively, if a mob is attacking at 75% of it's normal attack rate, you are taking 25% less damage than you otherwise would have taken had the mob's attack speed not been decreased.  Furthermore, slowing down a mob's attacks such that the time interval between blows is expanded is critical for casters who have to get off a spell uninterrupted. As for making the mallet "proc", try right-clicking on the mallet in combat with a mob targeted.  I don't know whether that will work.  </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
